76561198081886746,Recommended,251060,19180440,"Posted: 20 November, 2015",all,ViolentPlatypus,"Solid game. Having 16 years of gaming experience (across all platforms, genres, etc) I can easily say this is one of the best games I've ever played. It really is just a well rounded game.People who enjoy intense strategy will most likely enjoy this game. The learning curve is relatively steep. So my advice is player multiplayer, with the expectation you will be defeated constantly for your first month. But instead of quitting out of games, learn from the better players. Once you start getting a few key aspects down, it is not difficult to become a competent player.Matchmaking can be a little one sided at times. But remain positive... it is through failing and learning that'll you'll become a very good player. People don't master this over night.That all being said though, the game is still massively better then alot of other strategy games out there. And it is very easy to become absorbed by it. Community online is healthy.Id like to think after the disappointment I've seen around Act of Aggression, the developers will return to make another one of these games. Only time will tell - until then I'll keep enjoying this game.I highly recommend this game."
