,Recommended,251060,19290407,"Posted: 26 November, 2015",all,Vyntage,"Great game.You play as one of the many modern factions like America, Russia, China, Japan, Korea, British, Germany, etc and you build a 'deck' which is basically something you stuff with vehicles, infantry, naval units or air from that said faction or multiple factions. (Bonus to sticking to a single faction, and there is prebuilt decks for beginners)There is land, air and naval combat. The vehicles are realistic. There is fuel, detracking, getting your rotor shot out and your copter crashing into a tank column and blowing it up. There is ways to get fuel again, because you start with a FoB (or Forward Operations Base) which supplies your troops with ammo, fuel, repairs, etc. The jets come in off-map from an air field and do what they do, and can retreat back to the air field (if they make it) for repairs and ammo restocking.The maps are absolutely gigantic. The enviorment feels alive. You can hide your troops in the foliage, secure and use buildings, craters are left as permanent scars in maps from your wars (Just for the duration of the game, you won't go back into a map filled with craters from previous games) there are mountains, forests, plains, plateaus, rivers, lakes, oceans, you name it, it's there.It's balanced. Yes, factions may favor one type of unit over another, like (example only, not true) USA may favor Infantry and have better infantry than the French, but the French have better air support, etc. Everything has a counter. Air has anti air and other air units like fighters and attack helicopters. Bazookas and RPGs and jets and other helicopters for ground and naval and air for other naval.There is objectives, you get command vehicles to secure sectors in a map usually codenamed something like a military term such as Alpha, Bravo, Charlie, Delta. The more zones you control the more advantages you get such as new ways to bring in units to that zone instead of your FoB's location.The graphics are superb. Extremely realistic, and you can zoom in on ongoing battles and see from almost a 3rd person perspective.I definitely recommend it whole heartedly, it's a great game extremely addicting and very fun.9.9/10"
