me in my mind, if you loose horably because of a break through attack on one flank that you weren't watching close enough or the player in that sector was unable to defete it you can see why they were able to beat youIf you are sold now, please note that the game curently has some flaws, for example some nations do not have any upgraded infentry, where as most of the others have a basic pre 1980 form of infentry than a upgraded infentry from 1985 or 1990 with better eqipment and access to more advanced transports. However it has been confermed by the developers that some of the first DLC (which would suprise me if it cost you anything) releases will address this problem.That last paragraph has been mostly delt with, with the release of The Milionth Mile most (but not all) of the nations have had an infentry upgrade option added. Also added were land based anti ship missile systems."
,Not Recommended,251060,26317214,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,valk,"TL;DR: It could be the best real-time strategy game ever released, but it is just game which has so much lost potential.So, what's the story. When you starting this game for the first time your reaction is ""Wow! A lot of units! A lot of paremeters! A lot of different armies!"" Yeah, but... It is not super-realistic or thought-out game as it seems to be at the first glance. This game trying to be realistic sometimes, here is no tanks shooting each other on 30 meters like in CoH or whatever, but a lot of things are sacrificed to ""balance"" and it doesn't make game balance better. If you think that you can get multiple different experiences playing different types of armies, you are wrong. There is a few optimal choices while most of armies unable to achieve anything but hurt you.Eugen made the basic parts of the game long time ago. And they did really good job! But they stopped driving this game to make it better. Currently, only one guy is continuing to work on this game and oh man... that would be better if they stopped touching this game. That guy doesn't even play his game or play it very occasionally on very low level. It seems like once a quarter he's drinking something, opens excel file and doing balance changes randomly. Today german regular infantry dominate over against anything, tomorrow they are not even usable. Today Eastern Block and Commonwealth are the worst, tomorrow they are the best. Why? Because f*** you, players, that's why.Pros- Unique gameplay;- Decent replayability;- Decent number of strategies and tactics (but it's gotten repetitive and formularic at this point);- Matchmaking and rating system for 1v1.Cons- Poor support;- Poor balance (in multiple acpests, not just between Red and Blue forces);- A lot of mechanics that should be in the game are missing;- Lack of content (like online campaign, different game modes, different theatres, etc);- No map-generator or map-editor and existing maps are mediocre;- No matchmaking for team games + smallish community size = lobby sim;- Huge amount of minor faults (some of them are not very ""minor"").So, playing this game is a quite specific experience. It is fun to play through the first time and explore the game, but once you have gotten experienced enough there is nothing to catch up to here. It is too unfinished to play it competitively and too complicated and noob unfriendly to play it casually. I wouldn't recommend to waste your time on it."
