,Recommended,251060,15222534,"Posted: 5 April, 2015",all,Dahl,"This is quite possibly my favorite game of all-time. The game is an RTS in the same sense as the latest C&C4 (No real Base-building) Except it doesn't arbitrarily limit the number of units you can have. Maps are gigantic, battles are huge, and there are some aspects of it that everyone just loves. That being said, there are a few limitations that might drive some away. I'll address them below.Good:-Battles are gigantic-Amazing variety of Units-Free DLC-Large Map Replayability-Wide variety of countries available-Land, Air, and Sea combat-Immense experimentation possible-Challenging Campaigns-Multiplayer battles (TO THE MAX)Bad:-Sea is kind of half-baked and does not work realistically-Otomatic was never sold to Denmark (Hehe)-NO GOOD TUTORIAL!!!!I know a lot of people complain about this one, but to be honest there's really nothing there! The in-game tutorial explains what each value means, but it never really explains how to play the game well. Many people just come in without any knowledge whatsoever and pick units arbitrarily. It requires some pretty intensive effort from experienced players (Like myself) to actually help these new guys and give them a hand. There are plenty of resources available for them on steam, but it's not always obvious where to find these.-Planes are unrealistic as well-SPAAG ground range is arbitrarily set at 1050m (Except for otomatic which is 2100, down from 2275)-Tank Range maxxes out at 2275M (for no real reason)-Ships don't fire KE/AP Rounds!!! (like they do IRL!)Overall, I absolutely adore this game. The dings I gave it above are things most regular players won't care about or really notice. If you like RTS, you couldn't go wrong with purchasing this game and having a blast. Please read the tutorials after you do, and check out a guide or two! If you're still confused, ask someone like me who knows how to play the game well for advice! We're happy to train you new guys!"
