,Recommended,251060,10906192,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,Carl Hamilton,"I recommend this game because there isn't any compition to it.There is no other RTS which let's you play with this many units.Nor is there any RTS that deals with the cold war like this. If you play this game you will probably end up knowing a lot about military hardware from the cold war that you didn't know.That being said. There are some warnings to this game. Despite it being very unique, and still being worked on. I should point out a few things:1. Navy Is broken, don't get this game to play with ships, very little effort was put into them, and they do not function very well at all.2. All of the screenshots for this game on steam are fake. All of them, for example, Wheeled vehicles move faster on roads so in the screenshot where tracked and wheeled chinese AA units drive together, is litterally not possible in the game, since there is no fuction to make units move together at the same speed.3. There is no formation control at all. So if you want any formation you'll have to manage all your units one at a time.4. The game isn't particularly balanced, overall Western Forces has some huge advantages, they may not be obvious, but to competitive players they are blatant, hence why that 80% of competitive players play NATO. This has been the case since release and also in wargame ALB, so do not expect this to be fixed anytime soon, especially since the developer doesn't acknowledge overall balance concern raised by competitive players.5. This game has a lot of hidden statistics, some of the most imporant statistics are not displayed ingame, and in order to play the game efficiantly you HAVE to go on the forum, and do a lot of reading.Some pros to this now:1. Huge amount of units, you'll see how simplistic and silly, most games view on units are when claiming to be authentic.2. There are genuine differences in units, and they feel powerful mostly.3. The engine is pretty hardcore, unless you have litterally a thousand units on the map, this game runds extremely smooth in my oppinion.4. Despite the unbalances, the game has a lot of room for skill progression, if you have the wits for it, it's possible to be really good at this game, and in that case it doesn't matter what faction you play.5. If you are a nationalist this is probably the game of your wet dreams as you will be allowed to trash evil communists/capitalists with just about every land or air vehicle made in the Soviet Union, USA, western europe, east asia and oceania the past 40-50 years. Even as Denmark."
