76561198013219117,Recommended,251060,21675893,"Posted: 6 March, 2016",all,Alucard,"One of the better RTS games I've played. The only other RTS to give me the same rush on multiplayer would be World of Confict. you can feild massive amounts of troops to the battlefeild and if you do not use strategy can still be pushed back. Steamrolling is less susceptable in this game like you would see in company of hereos 2 when facing germans. If your being pushed back use your artillery to pound the land between them and you or if they have a strong defence soften them up with artillary and airstrikes. land marines and vehicles behind their lines, or air assualt infantry into towns to hold the line for a rapid defence. Use destroyers and frigates to pound the coast or smaller ships up rivers to handle pesky amphibious vehicles from sneaking on the other side of the river. The game has a vast arsenal of troops and even after 100+ hours in the game i have not explored all of the different nation's varying units and how to best use them. If your a strategy nut that likes real time over turn based ones this would be a must have for you.Pros:- Very good balanced units between Nato and block forces. you can enter a match and not feel that one side has an advantage over another towards victory.- Having supply lines has always been a nice touch. Dont expect to keep units in a fight for ever. Fuel, ammo, and armor will deterioate over time along with morale. keep them supplied with cargo trucks and cargo helis.-challenging campaigns.-very nice models of vehicles with good accurate weapon names and characteristics.- infantry actually has a role on the battlefeild and wont feel insignificant versus tanks, can do plenty of damage if used properly and are the best units to have when defending parts of the map. in urban environments they are second to none and you'll have to burn them out.Cons:-Ships are lacking somewhat in larger combat classes such as frigates and especially destroyers. No cruisers so don't look. its mostly corvette and smaller style ship warfare using anti-ship missiles enmass.- AI will always know where your command units are haha, does not matter if they are hidden. They will also artillary strike hidden units that sit in one spot too long even if they have yet to spot them.- Some balancing is needed in ground based AT missiles still, depending on who you ask the block forces seems to hold an advantage there as many of their tanks are equipped with them.Very good game. I'd give it a 9/10 easily."
