,Recommended,251060,25401836,"Posted: 7 September, 2016",all,sam,"Is it fun? Yes it is. This is possibly the most fun RTS game I've ever played. Its secret is in its depth and the UNBELEIVEABLE number of units to construct into army decks, which you then deploy directly onto the field with no base-building. This is the game that I play whenever I want to be reminded why I love RTS. It's the most unique and addictive game I've ever had the pleasure of getting stomped in.BUT...There are some caveats. The community on the in-game text chat is absolutely psychotic. There is no playable tutorial, just a set of text documents that tell you about the game mechanics and unit types. The difficulty curve is like trying to climb a 90 degree cliff while wearing roller skates, and for the first few hours you're not going to have any idea what is going on. And finally, the story campaigns are lackluster and honestly not what you're really there for.Are these deal breakers? No, they aren't. I still love this game in spite of its faults. It's a masochistically hard Real Time Strategy that shines like a beacon of innovation in a mostly stagnant genre. You simply have to play it just to see the incredible depth and intensity that RTS games can deliver."
