,Recommended,251060,10172577,"Posted: 19 May, 2014",all,Magpie (Szikra),"The best installment of the series IMHO.Highly recommended for anyone who is interested in intricate RTS games and military technology!An in-depth, somewhat realistic approach to modern warfare, with a relatively steep learning curve and a micro management intensive gameplay that will keep you pinned to the computer for hours. (Or scare you away, but do not be afraid! It is truly worth your patience).I absolutely love it. Make a deck/army to use out of more than a thousand units, different infantry sections and vehicle variants and then carefully manage your Leopard tank to rock Soviet armour... or set up an ambush with infantry waiting for the enemy vehicles to pass, just to active RPGs, when they can fire a devastating sideshot into weak parts of enemy armour.... there are lots of such tactical possibilites, thanks to the well thought-out combat system.This is not a rock-paper-scissor game like Starcraft. Just like in real life, every gun matters if properly used... no matter how elite your infantry is, it will get mowed down by the cheapest LMG on open ground, if you are not managing it properly and utilise cover and so aswell, the mightiest MBT can fall to auto cannon fire, should an IFV manage to sneak behind it.Truly a very enjoyable mix of reality and gameplay-balance decisions. I am sure everyone can find his way to fight in this game, especially in gigantic battles with 20 players, where everyone counts.Not to mention the absolutely stunning video engine, bringing great scaling and visuals, while retaining a good performance.A great game for every wholehearted strategy fan."
