76561198040401422,Recommended,251060,12009021,"Posted: 6 September, 2014",all,Dolor,"##START EDIT##I've been playing this some more, and I think I was being a little too hard on this game from the outset.  It is indeed very hard, but the rules aren't as obtuse as I initially thought.  That plus the fact that you can slow down time progression which is a huge improvement over the last game and a critical piece (for me) to playing this game, and I think I am switching to a mild qualified recommend.I think it may be too intense for my preferences (one small mistake and the scenario can be lost), but the merits of the game are pretty clear at this point.##END EDIT##The Good:- Beautifully detailed and realized large scale real-time strategy- Gorgeous graphically- RTS gameplay shows flashes of its brilliant potentialThe Bad:- Gameplay enjoyment is too often sacrificed for increased realism/difficulty- Realism is generally sacrificed in the simulation only to make the game more tedious/difficult (e.g. helicopters run out of fuel in minutes, lose a particular vehicle and you lose air support)Overall:I love the RTS genre, and most of my favorite games are RTS, but I can't recommend this game.  While it is obviously well made, it sacrifices too much ""fun"" for realism, difficulty, or tedium too often.I don't know if it's realistic for tanks to run out of ammo or helicopters to run out of gas in 5 minutes of fighting, but what I do know is that it sure as heck isn't fun."
