76561198037336600,Recommended,251060,11021148,"Posted: 2 July, 2014",all,uhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh,"This review has been completely updated as I wrote the first review with little understanding of the game. Previously I thought the land battles were good, but I liked the naval battles more. That has completely changed. The naval battels are quite bad, land is the only worthwhile part of this game. So first, the naval battles.Naval battles in a mixed land/water maps ussually handled by one person. It ussually ends up being blufor spamming anti-ship jets against redfor, or one of the sides will push towards the enemy spawn, and the enemy will have saved money and instantly spawn in 2-3 ships and destroy the aggressors. I have never had an actual naval battle on these maps. The closest I have come is missile stand offs. Occassionaly the navy will start bombarding land, and at this point you cant afford any sort of anti naval units, so it is just a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥ To conclude naval battles are essentially missile cheese battles.Land battles are far better. My only gripe is with high end tanks. They run for about 170-180 but are a little lackluster. If a tank 1 has 15 frontal armor and a gun that does 18 damage, and tank 2 has 22 frontal armor and a gun that does 20, the tank 1 will do one damage and tank 2 will do 5. This means Tank 1 kills tank 2 in ten hits and tank 2 kills tank 1 in two hits. This seems fair enough, but it means that heavy tanks can be damaged by any sort of semi heavy projectile, even shots from a 30mm auto cannon on a BTR-90. They are also destroyed extremely quickly by any sort of ATGM. Any sort of anti tank attack helo can kill these high end tanks with 23 frontal armor in 2-3 hits. Other than that I have no problems with the game. It manages to be realistic, but still faced paced at the same time. Just make sure you play conquest, Destruction modes are essentially world war 1 all over again."
