76561198020477852,Not Recommended,251060,17571723,"Posted: 16 August, 2015",all,BigMeatSpecial,"First off, by my hours played on not only this game but the others in the series you can tell I am(was) a fan of the Wargame series.I dont really write reviews but for a game series which ive cared about so very much I feel I must.I really cant recommend this game to an avid strategy fan. The other 2 games, European Escalation and Airland Battle I can, but not this one.The biggest problem with this game, and it has been like this since launch, is the artillery. In the past games, Eugen(the developers), have wrestled with artillery and how much damage and stun it can do to units. In EE the artillery was very powerful but if played well it wasnt a real hindrance to other players. In Airland battle the nerf bat hit artillery pretty good, it left artillery in a state for being good for smoking or maybe pouring on stun for an assualt, but not overwhelmingly so.Now Wargame Red Dragon. Oh boy, they opened a can of worms on this one. MLRS and Cluster shot (Artillery which fragments in air and rains down like a cluster bomb) is the metagame in the large player games (10v10, 6v6, ect). If you bring a few cards of cluster and are somewhat competent, you can destroy a whole line of units, completely obliterating an enemies line of defense, opening the way for an assault. Now see,in a 1v1 or 2v2 or even 4v4 this isnt too bad, people are generally moving units around and making sure they arent in one place for along time. But the problem arises in the 10v10 games. if 2 or 3 or even 4 people all bring cluster artillery, it turns into a spamfest. You cant bring your units any where close to the front line without heavy tanks getting popped ina few shots by cluster artillery, and in long games it just doesnt stop.Now this isnt how artillery should be used in a game. It shouldnt be a god button for destroying hard units and removing assault lines, it should be used to somewhat stun and lower morale in the units on the front line to soften up for an assault by combined forces. Not to completely obliterate the whole line. But thats only one problem with it.In large games their is no real regulation on decks, if half the team brings a support(Artillery) deck, who's supply do you think they will use to refill their artillery after their Forward Operating Base(FOB) is depleted? DING DING DING Its going to be yours. Now that your FOB is depleted and you cant refuel and resupply your actual units, you know, those things called infantry, tanks, IFV's, and other front line units. Your line will be destroyed. But its okay because by that time your teammates will have cluster bombed the enemy into oblivion and everyone will have quit the 10v10!!!!!!!GG Eugen, this on top of other balance issues i wont go into have made this game thoroughly unenjoyable for those who like larger games."
