,Recommended,251060,9624478,"Posted: 24 March, 2014",all,iMainYORICKx420x,"Bigger, Badder, BetterI love how this game completely expands upon its predecessors. While Airland Battle felt more like a rectified and updated European Escalation, this feels like an all out war for top sequel. The game practically hands you all these different units and says, ""Go have fun.""I love how units do not rout as easily, either. There are so many factors that can decide the outcome of a battle. Because of the lessened rout, the little guy has a chance to make the difference. One panicked tank is able to harass an enemy column long enough for me to reinforce it.Never have I had so much fun blowing through enemy units or losing mine in a single, decisive swoop by my opponets. It keeps you thinking quick but always two steps ahead. What are you willing to sacrifice? When should you retreat? How will you make your advance?The Naval aspect opens new doors. Just this morning, I used an amphibious assault to take my opponent's point. Using Infantry and LAVs, I was able to distract the enemy invasion from taking siege of my ally. When they turned their heads, I swung my sword for the killing blow. My ally poured his reserves into those countless PACT units. My aircraft finished what was left. It might as well have been the Highway of Death on that map. What an invigorating experience and a sweet victory.This game is now my favorite of all three Wargames. Great job to the devs. Who's with me?"
