76561198081754614,Recommended,251060,11707973,"Posted: 14 August, 2014",all,TheQuadfather,"Wargame: Red Dragon is like the ArmA of the RTS universe. It's straight-up unparalleled. The in-game models, the gameplay mechanics, the necessity of combined-arms warfare, as well as the introduction of naval combat... Absolutely stunning. If you're into Real Time Strategy games, this can't be missed. It breaks out of the well-ridden World War II-era and brings RTS into the late 20th Century in mind-blowing fashion. The only downside I can really say is the lack of mod-ability, which leads into the four separate campaigns (based on partly fictional flashpoints in the late 20th Century) being kind of monotonous after being beaten two or three times (although the ever-changing, dynamic strategic map idea should be continued). If you like the idea of this, check out the previous two games in the series (also based around Cold War flashpoints), Wargame: European Escalation and Wargame: AirLand Battle."
