,Not Recommended,251060,11975337,"Posted: 4 September, 2014",all,Outcast,"Played some multiplayer before, often only with friends, tried the single player campaign. As always, step learning. Watched this game pretty much from day 1. Dident play Wargame: European Escalation at all, but i did play Wargame: Airland Battle and that was a great game. From what i understand alot of units from European Escalation was just ported into Wargame, so some units lacked detail.And here we are, with Red Dragon. Naval warfare galore it seems, but alas. No. I expected each country to have their own naval units, but instead each side shares their boats, so Blufor and opfor get their 15 or so boats, and every country can access all boats. That means that armies from like Scandinavia can use the Oliver Hazard Perry as their boat if they feel like it.There aren't alot of boats out there even, which sucks. For a game that boost about 1400 and something units it just feels... rushed. So it fails to deliver on that front. We do however get 4 new faction or so, and some alliance choices. You can now create decks of units from the commonwealth army or why not use scandinavian units et.c.Gameplay still feels like Airland Battle, nothing really new here. They told about terrain diffrences and that hills can block your line of sight and such, haven't really noticed anything diffrent from Airland Battle.And it might just be me but would'nt it be time to update the models abit. There are alot, and i mean alot of errors and problems in the models. Some examples are :Aircraft that are sunken abit into the ground when you create your decks (Landing gear clips through ground).Aircraft have payloads that are so large so they clip through the ground.Still uses models from European Escalation. Good examples are helicopters, some lack interiors all together. Some have interiors but no pilots, while newer helicopters have interiors and pilots.Many infantry units are portraited wrong ingame, sure you rarely play this game zoomed in but heres an example. The Swedish M90 uniform was formely introduced in the 1990, But was already in use since 1985. Wargame: Red Dragon is a game that spawns from 1970 to 1992 atleast. If we go after Eugen way of doing everything the easy way, why not butcher the U.S. Marine infantry model (They wear somewhat modern armor and BDU:s), arm them with the AK4 Rifle and just make a reskin so they use the M90 pattern? Easy as pie. (I know this might be slightly biased cause im from sweden, but as i see it, if i can find errors in a country representing my own, then others will do the same with their own countries)There are also some bugs here ande there, units that don't load in correctly, most units are just reskins of tanks from other nations et.c. Those skins are often portraited wrong, many of the nations camo dosen't even match (wasent there something called uniformity in the armed forces). I mean should'nt every nations unit look like they camed from the same place, instead of having some units colored in desert camo. Some in olive drab, some in digital camo et.c.These are mostly visual errors, the game has some bad problems with balancing. And suprise, suprise, the ♥♥♥♥♥♥ community from ALB has moved over to Red Dragon, new players will have an hard time getting help, bashing is to be expected and if thats not happening then theres always someone spamming the chat with flag emotes.And lastly, i find it hard to believe there are actully 1400+ diffrent units in the game. Most infantry can be ordered in diffrent transports. Are all those diffrent variations classed as a unit? I believe that's how they count. If someone actully counted all units (excluding their transport options) i'd bet there are alot fewer units to choose from.Can i recommend this game? No. Sorry, i really can't. It's nothing special, Airland Battle feelt like a more complete game all in all. At the time of writing this, the game was on -50% sale (19,99€). And i can't really tell if this is a reasonable price for this game... maybe, i guess? Get it if you feel like it for that price, or hope for an even better sale. Play it with friends, do not expect to much and well... maybe, just maybe you'll have a good time for a couple of games or two."
