,Recommended,251060,9857424,"Posted: 17 April, 2014",all,SilEighty,"Long time RTS player here, going all the way back to the Close Combat series.  I'm always keeping an eye out for strategy wargames that focus on *realism* - engagements taking place at real distances, where terrain matters, etc., but are still FUN.After Close Combat there was one hell of a drought--for years.  Combat Mission was good, but (sort of) turn based and the visuals were...lacking.  Later, Company of Heroes looked promising, but ultimately played just like Starcraft.  The Men of War series was probably the best thing in realistic wargaming for a while until this series got wrapped up in its impossible campaigns and petered out.Wargame (this one AND the prior one) has a huge (but not overwhelming) scale, realistic scope, meticulously detailed units.  Infantry movement isn't at the level of detail of a Close Combat game, but that's acceptable given the scale.  This game is brutal, but the community (the game launches to a menu with an already-active chat window) is helpful and entertaining.  Honestly, nobody is very good.  This is the sort of game that you'd probably need a stint at West Point or Quantico to be truly great at.  But that's the fun: the multplayer games are a satisfying length of slamming around the map hoping (if you're like me) that someone on your team knows what they're doing more than you do.It's hard, but the menu isn't too complex.  Your units go, they stop, they land (if they're a helicopter).  It's not ""Micro"" that makes you good, it's deploying them intelligently...You'll spend as much time customizing your army ""decks"" as you do playing, and you'll enjoy every second of it.Last note: this game takes truly amazing screenshots.  And yes, it DOES look that good, but in the heat of battle, combined with dubious camera controls, you'll rarely be looking at your units that closely.  Wish the camera was snappier so you could zoom around and see those amazingly detailed units up close more often.Last last note: The second Wargame title (Air Land Battle) added airplanes, which the first game didn't have.  This one adds boats.  They're nifty and look great, but they're expensive so it is very sad when they sink, which they will."
