76561197986775314,Recommended,251060,15188410,"Posted: 3 April, 2015",all,Aluminum Elite Master,"This is an under-rated game.It definitely is a little less on the production quality than some RTS games, and is certainly not a game with a vast number of players.But it is a RTS game with a slower pace and more mechanics at play than usual for RTS games. This is a welcome thing for those of us who are no longer in their teens and get less of a kick from being in a mad rush all match long. Plus, the slower pace opens the door to mechanics like supply and recon. Units eventually use up all their ammo and need to resupply, while recon needs to be conducted before sending other types of units into an area of the map.It's not a perfect game, and it does suffer from sort of repetative map design and fairly inconsistent AI. But multiplayer is the meat of the game, and aside from some latency issues that crop up from time to time, the multiplayer is pretty good and allows for more thinking than reacting, which for a RTS is a breath of fresh air.Again, by no means a perfect game, and definitely not overly polished in terms of music and UI, but certainly a game worth having for strategy gamers, particularly those who prefer a bit more though and a bit less reflexes."
