,Recommended,251060,11607637,"Posted: 8 August, 2014",all,BottlenekDolfin,"(like, 200 hours multiplayer or something) How do I describe this game? It's a slow paced, high learning curve, RTS. Unlike Starcraft where APM is the most important, out thinking and deceiving is the objective in this game. Playing defensively is often very effective as that most unit's have hard counters that are very effective at their job. ATGM easily kills tanks, Anti-air often easily kills aircraft and helicopters. Infantry can not be caught in the open.In short, this game is all about positioning. It's like real time chess and every unit you control is some aspect of rock/paper/scissors. Except there is a ton of stats and stuff to geek out on.TL;DR If you enjoy RTS and are willing to get through the learning curve, $40 will get you easily 200+ hours in muliplayer. This game is well worth the money. Also try to join a teamspeak group."
