76561197968544038,Recommended,251060,12146256,"Posted: 19 September, 2014",all,BrainySmurf,"A lot of potential here but ultimately the game doesn't deliver for a number of reasons. With games like this developers often have to compromise between gameplay balance and realism, Wargame seems to fail at both. Also, many of the concepts are totally non-intuitive, balance is not as great as it could be, and tactics that seem intuitive often fail. Accuracy is arbitrary and specific effects (like panic) are unrealistic and random. All that said with some balance patches and time I think this could be a great game. If one aspect is the doom of this game it has to be the ridiculous micromanagement. In a game that bills itself as a real strategic simulator, you will spend 90% of your time calling in fighters are precisely the right moment, telling your marines to move out of mortar fire, or you tanks to back up into cover while under fire. For me, that makes it essentially a babysitting simulator. Basic AI or a more robust command menu where you could issue conditional commands would let players actually sit back and think about tactics, unit compositions, and angles of attack, rather than telling a platoon leader to move out of the napalm."
