meplay is nice but there could be more options in formations and  behavior.The consThe balance between nations armies are another topic that migth complicate, like the sweden army is balanced so it can face the soviet army in simple words, but all games(exclusively the strategy ones, save a few ones) have this issue we like or not. For a realistic game this con weighs a lot.The time limit battles that happens in both the single and multiplayer, the multiplayer limit is understandable but the singleplayer sometimes it gives the nerves mainly if you want to try something different or use that unit or because in order to win the battle you have to get a high ponctuantion to get victory nor a draw.I a recommend this game to anyone that looks for a more deep strategy game that use 20 century weaponry and that you command everything from infantry squads to regiments and from ships to fleets."
