76561198049449791,Recommended,251060,23118911,"Posted: 21 May, 2016",all,Godphila,"I love this game. And let me tell you something: It is hard (Maybe because I am sh*t at strategy, but that's another topic). I gave my enemy a very bad deck of units, and set their A.I. To Easy, and they almost kicked my ... you know.The Pros:-The Unit selection is extremly big, with Units from Every nation, from Sweden to South Korea, from Czechia to North Korea. Each Nation has Tanks, Infantry (with Authentic Names), Artillery, Jets, Anti Tanks Unit, Ships, Helicopters, Commandvehicles, Recon Units and Supports (Several Nations share units, of course, but that is unavoidable)-The Units are very detailed, and are well balanced. The better a unit is, the more it costs, and the lower is the maximal number of untis of this type you can own.-Combat is fast and brutal. There is not much time to decide and improvise when you encounter your Enemy. Every Unit has Moral, which influences their behavior.-And most of all, it's very realistic. You have no idea what your enemy is doing, except through reconnaissance. If you don't have reconnaissance, you loose. There is no radius showing you how far your recon units can see, which always gives you the feeling of missing enemy movements.-The possibility to make a deck from ALL nations (of course only from either West or East, no mix-ups) is really really cool.-Full-fledged Cover system-The graphics is simply gorgeous.The Cons (Which are fairly few, because I almost always happy with games):-The Sea combat is very much improvable. There are not much sounds, the unit selection is small (Compared to the rest of the game), and the russians CIWS Systems are overpowered.-It's often difficult to command troops, as they all have different speeds, so the weak support and recon go ahead, and on enemy contact get instantly wrecked. There are no formations out of which you could choose to improve the survivability of units.-The Experience System has no influence what so ever.But this game is the wet dream of every Strategy Gamer who loves realism. If you don't have this game, get it. But wait for a sale, because 40€ are still a little much xD"
