76561198066508250,Recommended,251060,24381529,"Posted: 17 July, 2016",all,General Alex,"Its a good game overall, frustrating at times, but on the whole its pretty good. I reccomend it to people who owned Airland Battle and other RTS outsiders. The simple point system means you can focus entirely on the combat side of things and not have to worry about base building or upgrades or anything like that. Dont buy into a units stats alone. Weaker units can kill stronger units if positioned correctly ( or if your oponent has no idea what they are doing). The enormous range of deck combinations is pretty awesome because you feel like its ""your"" army you are playing with. Your tanks, your troops, your planes. Dont make a ton of different armies because you will never use all of them and if you do you will constantly be trying to remember what goes where. Better to have a couple armies and then really get to know them.P.S Please dont spam artillery, I dont mind if you use it,but dont make an all arty support deck.P.S.S All of the above is my personal experience playing the game and if other people have had other experiences thats just fine. Im just trying to give some advice."
