,Recommended,251060,15493663,"Posted: 22 April, 2015",all,[OpFor] Ghost,"A great game, that pisses you off, but is sooo addictive.You will most probably want to play this game for the multiplayer, considering the AI is pretty bland.And multiplayer can be amazing or it can be a Cluster ♥♥♥♥, depends on who is on your team really.Not a game you want to just throw your troops at the enemy, You need to think, addapt and cooperate to win.It features a good amount of different countries to fight with and against, devided in Blue and Red, blue being NATO or those allied with it in some way and Red being Warsaw Pact with those that would Ally with them, China, North korea ...each countries troops have similarties to each other and also big differences, in what they can use as material for example. for example West Germany has Leopard2A5 and the French have the Leclerc.the interesting part about this game, for me, is that you make a 'deck' of troops (think like making a deck in a card game)before you enter a battle, in the battle you have a certain amount of points that you can spend to 'place' these troops on the battlefield or later during the battle, call them in as reinforcements. Each troop has a certain amount of points cost, for example: early tanks that are not that good will be cheaper than the best of the line and last produced tanks.You also have a fixed amount of troops you have to your disposal,for example you can only call in 12 leopards2a1. so using them wisely and being carefull when and where to use them makes a difference. Not only in the fact taht you have a limited amount of troops usually the games goal is to destroy a certain amount of 'points' of the enemy team. for example destroy 1000 points of enemy troops to win. so destryoing a tank that costs the enemy 180 points is great, compared to only a tank of 20 points. vice versa the lose is also worse if it's a good, expensive tank.You can have all sorts of troops in the game. ranging from infantry and tanks, to airplanes, ships and logistical units, which is to say that logistical units are a very important part of the game. you will need to ressuply your troops with ammo, fuel and repairs. Although this seems like a hassle, it's actually done in an easy, straightforward way, that yet keeps the tactical and strategical importance of logistics inside the game.there's a lot more to be said about this game. Id say go watch a let's play to get a better understanding of it, it's easy yet has depth to it."
