,Recommended,251060,33825415,Posted: 26 July,all,LionofLannister,"This is an ultra-realistic wargame.  If you are looking for a Command and Conquer or Starcraft style game, this is not it. I used to think I was an amazing general, the second coming General Patton or Rommel. This game made me realize there is more to warfare than securing the most resources and pumping out the most troops. I’ve had an armada of tanks wiped out because I charged in without securing the high ground. I’ve had planes shot out of the sky because I underutilized my reconnaissance. To put it simply, if you fancy yourself a strategic mind, then buy this game. It will test your intelligence and common sense. This is the first and only game to really make me feel like a General."
,Recommended,251060,33842218,Posted: 27 July,all,The Quill Guy,"Again, not really any other games like this one, so recommended for that reason with reservation.Even on the easy AI (which on other RTS games gives you some space to breathe), the computer will swarm the map and take all the points.There are dozens of units named only by seven-digit numbers, each with specific roles to play. The game doesn't help you out with that.The tutorial is laughably non-existent, consisting of five pages of text.For the length of time necessary to get something out of this game, an equivalent effort with an actual tutorial and some help with what units do would be useful.I appreciate that the game is purposefully difficult, and that war is meant to be neither fair or easy. But the amount of time I think I'm expected to play on this just to make some workable combinations, and the lack of a beginner AI means that the game really requires a lot of investment to become fun.Read the positive reviews from those who are better than me at this game for what the game is like should you persevere."
