76561197970816016,Recommended,251060,10874504,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,Darkin,"This is what I first thought after an hour of playing it-Unplayably complicated with no tutorial, this game drops you into the fight straight at the deep end. The ""tutorial"" on the menu screen is basicly the manual, and you better read and understand it first go because you can't get to it ingame. If you want to spend two hours trying to figure out why you have no troops to command or lose thirty seconds in, buy this game. If you want a decent Real Time Stratery game, look elsewhere. I'm sorry I atually paid money for it.- UpdatedBecause I paid for it, I stuck with it. It took me about five hours of blundering around and re-reading the tutorial section, but I finally worked out the resource mechanics, how you have to secure sectors to call for reinforcements and the incredably complicated rock-paper-sissors system of weapons and counter weapons. I am, at last, enjoying it, although I still think it desperately needs some better introductions for new players. I have had some stabilty issues with crashing graphics, but infrequently, its not a massive problem.Overall, its a pretty decent, highly complex, combat simulator. Be prepared to sink a few hours into reading the online player guides, and more hours into learning the systems by losing repeatedly. This game will eat your time up.-UPDATED 183 HOURS LATEROk, I get it now.Only took what, two, four years to master? My biochemistry degree took longer to earn that that! A mere instant! totally worth it!final review - really really micro intense RTS with endless complications. Really hard to master, frustrating, built for people who already know how to play it. Fun when you do."
