,Recommended,251060,35382087,Posted: 1 October,all,Sir Winston Churchill,"Napalm works on water 11/10Problem in MP is that u don't get enough points to buy stuff so you are kind of forced into low budget guerilla warfare.Also - and this is probably the biggest issue - Pivads are the most overpowered thing there is, along with the Czech Dana Artillery and Israeli and Finnish Napalm MLRSs.Also the REDFOR Navy is waaaay better than the junky 1 Kongo and 6 Fremantles you can spawn when playing as NATO and the SU-27 is... just overpowered. It can fire it's rockets from a distance of 2 km or so and they almost always hit.I really like AirLand Battle more, tho it got way less attention at EUGEN than Red Dragon and therefore you have less vehicles there.So to sum it all up: It is indeed a good game and worth buying, but it is quite unbalanced and the campaign is unplayable - Even I as what I would call a veteran of Eugen's games haven't even managed to beat the easiest mission."
